02:27.939 --> 02:31.614
<i>TV REPORTER: In a related story, the
high court had also refused to stay</i>

02:31.693 --> 02:35.539
<i>Friday's execution of former
philosophy professor David Gale.</i>

02:35.739 --> 02:38.834
<i>Gale had sought a review
of his 1994 conviction</i>

02:38.909 --> 02:42.004
<i>for the rape and murder of his
University of Austin colleague,</i>

02:42.079 --> 02:43.501
<i>Constance Harraway.</i>

02:43.580 --> 02:46.174
<i>The case has received
nationwide media attention</i>

02:46.249 --> 02:49.879
<i>because Gale and Harraway
were activists for Death Watch,</i>

02:49.961 --> 02:52.259
<i>a nonprofit abolitionist
organization.</i>

02:52.339 --> 02:57.266
<i>Do you understand how much money taxpayers
pay in Texas to put one person to death?</i>

02:57.386 --> 03:00.139
<i>What do we want?
ALL: No more executions!</i>

03:00.263 --> 03:03.483
<i>DAVID: Governor, can't we all admit
the capital punishment system</i>

03:03.558 --> 03:04.980
<i>in this country is not working?</i>

03:05.060 --> 03:07.859
They're not going to stay Gale.
It's on TV right now. Listen.

03:07.938 --> 03:09.781
<i>Defense lawyers
had hoped to argue</i>

03:09.856 --> 03:12.735
<i>that Gale's former activism
against capital punishment</i>

03:12.818 --> 03:15.537
<i>unduly prejudiced
the Texas judicial system.</i>

03:15.612 --> 03:19.116
The deal was Bitsey would get the
interview if the stay was refused.

03:19.199 --> 03:21.327
He'll talk to her for
two hours a day,

03:21.410 --> 03:23.538
Tuesday, Wednesday
and Thursday.

03:24.079 --> 03:25.831
Can't do Friday. No.

03:26.415 --> 03:28.258
Friday's the day
they execute him.

03:29.835 --> 03:31.883
The lawyer said only Bitsey.

03:31.962 --> 03:33.635
Gale's going down.
Shh!

03:34.506 --> 03:36.600
Only Bitsey means only Bitsey.

03:36.675 --> 03:38.143
I don't get to
make the rules, Joe.

03:38.218 --> 03:39.765
Please, I'm a fat black woman.

03:39.845 --> 03:42.348
What we need is to put
her on a plane to Texas.

03:42.806 --> 03:44.558
Why do you get like
that around legal?

03:44.641 --> 03:46.689
Hold on, we're coming over.

03:49.229 --> 03:51.698
What's this "Only Bitsey
means only Bitsey" stuff?

03:51.773 --> 03:53.946
They asked for you,
and no substitutes.

03:54.025 --> 03:56.073
Who's they, exactly?
Gale's lawyers.

03:56.153 --> 03:59.783
More exactly, Gale's lawyer.
Some good old boy in Austin.

03:59.865 --> 04:01.082
Why do they want me?

04:01.158 --> 04:02.375
You don't want the assignment?

04:02.492 --> 04:03.744
I'm not saying that.

04:03.827 --> 04:06.171
I can't see why a guy
about to be executed

04:06.246 --> 04:07.623
should suddenly ask for me.

04:07.706 --> 04:10.960
Maybe they liked your kiddie
porn piece, and going to jail.

04:11.042 --> 04:13.511
Maybe he saw your picture
and thinks you're cute.

04:13.587 --> 04:15.260
So how much access do I get?

04:15.380 --> 04:17.007
Three interviews.
No time for more.

04:17.089 --> 04:18.808
By Friday, the guy's a goner.

04:19.634 --> 04:21.386
What exactly is our story?

04:21.511 --> 04:23.309
Rape, murder, death row.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.775
Very intelligent guy.
Maybe he's even innocent.

04:26.850 --> 04:28.227
Yeah, right.

04:29.144 --> 04:31.522
JOE: No, tell him I'll
call him back. Thanks.

04:31.855 --> 04:33.448
BARBARA: So what's
your problem?

04:33.523 --> 04:36.993
JOE: Hi, Barbara. Morning, Bitsey.
Okay, here's my concern.

04:37.360 --> 04:38.782
Setting aside the cost issue,

04:38.862 --> 04:42.116
although $500,000 in cash
for three days of interviews

04:42.199 --> 04:44.167
is not only illegal,
it's obscene.

04:44.242 --> 04:46.995
That's market value.
The guy's never talked.

04:47.078 --> 04:50.628
Aside from that, I, we are still
uncomfortable with the arrangement.

04:50.957 --> 04:51.958
Why?

04:52.042 --> 04:54.636
You just spent a very
public seven days in jail

04:54.711 --> 04:56.964
for a very public
contempt-of-court citation.

04:57.047 --> 05:00.551
For protecting sources. If you
were uncomfortable with the story,

05:00.634 --> 05:03.353
why did you slap it on the
domestic and international covers?

05:03.428 --> 05:07.478
What makes us uncomfortable
is that a rapist/murderer

05:07.557 --> 05:09.901
has asked to spend the last
three days of his life

05:09.976 --> 05:12.274
giving an interview,
his very first,

05:12.354 --> 05:13.947
to a reporter who is now famous

05:14.064 --> 05:15.657
for protecting sexual deviants.

05:15.732 --> 05:18.406
A reporter who is also
a very attractive woman.

05:18.485 --> 05:20.112
This is disparate treatment.

05:20.237 --> 05:21.830
JOE: Oh, boy.

05:21.905 --> 05:23.657
I could go if I
were an ugly guy?

05:23.740 --> 05:27.040
The agenda issue would be diffused
with the presence of a male.

05:27.118 --> 05:29.496
I hear lawyers
gleefully saying,

05:29.621 --> 05:31.999
"Bloom versus
<i>News Magazine</i> Inc."

05:32.082 --> 05:34.631
"Your Honor, I started
to notice my assignments

05:34.709 --> 05:36.962
"were being determined
on the basis of my sex."

05:37.045 --> 05:38.672
You've got to let her go now.

05:38.755 --> 05:40.007
That's not what I meant.

05:40.131 --> 05:41.428
He's got to let you go.

05:41.508 --> 05:43.602
All right. Enough.

05:43.677 --> 05:46.351
But the intern will be
with you at all times.

05:46.429 --> 05:48.147
What? Intern.

05:48.265 --> 05:50.814
No, you've got to be kidding.
That's what he said.

05:50.892 --> 05:52.519
He's a jerk.
He's the boss.

05:52.602 --> 05:54.650
Not an intern.
I always work alone.

05:54.729 --> 05:55.855
Not this time, Bitsey.

05:55.939 --> 05:57.316
I'm not baby-sitting.

06:13.790 --> 06:17.169
BITSEY: Gale's DNA was everywhere.
His semen was inside her.

06:17.252 --> 06:18.845
He was seen leaving her house.

06:18.920 --> 06:21.890
His prints were all over the
kitchen, including one on the bag.

06:21.965 --> 06:23.387
Half a thumbprint.

06:23.508 --> 06:24.976
Half a thumbprint.
That's enough.

06:25.051 --> 06:27.520
He could've touched it before
it was a murder weapon.

06:27.596 --> 06:29.564
You fondle your
friends' garbage bags?

06:29.639 --> 06:32.188
Yeah, I get very touchy
around household plastics.

06:32.267 --> 06:34.235
I'm particularly
fond of Tupperware.

06:34.311 --> 06:35.528
Tupperware?

06:35.604 --> 06:39.825
I'm just saying the bag could've
been sitting on the counter.

06:40.984 --> 06:43.578
He did it. Now he's going to die.
And you know something?

06:43.653 --> 06:45.621
Maybe that's exactly
what he deserves.

06:45.697 --> 06:47.745
But the murder's way
too fucking clumsy.

06:47.824 --> 06:52.000
This guy is an intellectual. Top of
his Harvard class, Rhodes Scholar,

06:52.078 --> 06:54.752
tenured at 27,
two books published.

06:54.831 --> 06:56.504
He's an academic stud.

06:56.625 --> 06:59.174
Look at his wife.
A regular Grace Kelly.

06:59.753 --> 07:02.802
Old money svelte. Father
was ambassador to Spain.

07:02.881 --> 07:04.849
Shit! The light's on again.

07:04.966 --> 07:06.843
Ignore it, it's a rental.

07:07.218 --> 07:08.845
Do you smell anything?

07:08.970 --> 07:10.597
The guy's a flaming Liberal.

07:10.680 --> 07:12.432
A person's politics
has nothing to do

07:12.515 --> 07:13.607
with his tendency
to commit crime.

07:13.725 --> 07:14.772
Wrong.

07:14.851 --> 07:16.774
Shouldn't it smell
if it's overheating?

07:16.853 --> 07:19.777
Seventy-three percent of all
serial killers vote Republican.

07:19.856 --> 07:22.234
Throw your cigarette out,
so we can smell.

07:24.319 --> 07:26.117
You'll stink up the car.
Throw it out.

07:26.196 --> 07:27.994
I'm not going to
fucking pollute.

07:43.838 --> 07:46.557
BITSEY: There's definitely
something wrong with this car.

07:46.633 --> 07:47.976
This is so irritating.

07:48.051 --> 07:49.473
How far to Huntsville?

07:49.552 --> 07:51.429
BITSEY: I'm going to pull off.

07:52.222 --> 07:55.101
<i>"News Magazine</i> reporters
Bitsey Bloom and Zack Stemmons

07:55.183 --> 07:56.981
"entered the rest
area with car troubles.

07:57.060 --> 07:58.687
"Little did they know it wasn't

07:58.812 --> 08:00.405
"just their car
that was in trouble."

08:01.898 --> 08:04.242
I'm a reporter.
You're an intern.

08:06.820 --> 08:07.912
Whatever.

08:23.878 --> 08:25.095
Is it hot?

08:25.797 --> 08:28.050
Jesus, yes!
Isn't it always?

08:29.342 --> 08:30.685
What do I do?

08:30.760 --> 08:33.764
Call the office and get the
rental road service number.

08:36.599 --> 08:37.725
No signal.

08:37.851 --> 08:38.943
God damn it.

08:40.020 --> 08:41.272
I've got to pee.

09:03.585 --> 09:04.586
Zack!

09:07.130 --> 09:08.131
Zack!

09:08.214 --> 09:09.466
Yeah?

09:58.598 --> 10:00.145
Morning.
Hi.

10:03.353 --> 10:05.321
A little early
for that, isn't it?

10:05.897 --> 10:08.070
The nonsmoking
section's over there.

10:08.441 --> 10:10.114
I meant the book.

10:10.735 --> 10:12.954
<i>Dialogical Exhaustion</i>
by David Gale.

10:13.822 --> 10:15.290
The guy's a genius.

10:15.990 --> 10:17.037
What time is it?

10:17.158 --> 10:18.205
9:15 a.m.

10:19.035 --> 10:20.833
There are 10
prisons around here.

10:20.954 --> 10:22.706
Death row is in the Ellis unit,

10:22.789 --> 10:25.963
but they're moving it to the Terrell
unit at the end of the year.

10:26.042 --> 10:27.794
The waitress's
boyfriend works there.

10:27.877 --> 10:30.130
Her last boyfriend worked
in the Huntsville unit.

10:30.213 --> 10:32.056
The two before that in Walker.

10:32.132 --> 10:34.305
The Estelle unit
has the cutest guys.

10:34.384 --> 10:38.434
And I'm quoting, "My butt's too
big to get an Estelle guy."

10:40.723 --> 10:42.316
Ellis is 15 minutes
out of town.

10:42.433 --> 10:44.060
We've got five
and a half hours.

10:44.144 --> 10:47.239
Never eat in a place where the
menus have pictures of the food.

10:47.564 --> 10:50.238
We should drive into Austin.
Check out the crime scene.

10:50.316 --> 10:52.910
That could be some
great stuff for our story.

10:52.986 --> 10:56.581
This isn't our story. It's not even
a story. It's an interview.

10:57.532 --> 11:00.911
Most importantly for you to
remember, it's my interview.

11:02.579 --> 11:05.002
What do I do for
the next five hours?

11:05.081 --> 11:07.630
Drive around. Look for
a decent restaurant.

11:10.211 --> 11:13.090
Your reputation as
Mike Wallace with PMS

11:13.173 --> 11:14.675
doesn't do you justice.

11:15.049 --> 11:16.847
My reputation got
us invited here.

11:16.926 --> 11:19.679
I play by the rules, even if
my colleagues don't like it.

11:19.762 --> 11:21.355
It's called...
Ambition?

11:21.431 --> 11:22.432
Objectivity.

11:22.515 --> 11:23.767
What can I get you, ma'am?

11:23.892 --> 11:25.109
Just coffee.

11:29.731 --> 11:31.199
Don't push me, smart ass.

11:46.956 --> 11:48.629
You know you're
in the Bible belt

11:48.708 --> 11:50.836
when there are more
churches than Starbucks.

11:50.919 --> 11:53.297
When there are more
prisons than Starbucks.

12:39.342 --> 12:40.844
(DOOR BUZZES OPEN)

13:14.168 --> 13:16.011
He's ready for y'all now.

13:16.212 --> 13:17.338
GROVER: Yes, I am.

13:20.967 --> 13:25.313
I'm not gonna debate with you the
rights and wrongs of the situation.

13:26.055 --> 13:28.558
Our job is to run the
state prison system.

13:30.476 --> 13:33.901
This is not France. This is not
Germany. This is Texas.

13:33.980 --> 13:36.074
And we're gonna
follow Texas law.

13:36.941 --> 13:39.364
You're very welcome, ma'am.
Goodbye, now.

13:40.528 --> 13:41.905
Thank you, Margie.

13:42.488 --> 13:45.412
Correspondents Bloom and
Stevens, I presume?

13:45.491 --> 13:46.788
Yes, hello.

13:47.243 --> 13:48.745
Stemmons.

13:48.911 --> 13:50.413
Sorry.
Won't happen again.

13:50.621 --> 13:53.340
I'm Duke Grover, TDCJ,
Community Relations.

13:53.416 --> 13:55.544
He's usually real
good with names.

13:55.626 --> 13:58.220
And these days I
always like to ask

13:58.296 --> 14:00.674
do you prefer Miss,
Mrs., or Ms.?

14:01.257 --> 14:02.383
Bitsey.

14:02.508 --> 14:03.555
Bitsey it is.

14:03.634 --> 14:04.931
Margie, I'm stealing
your guests.

14:05.053 --> 14:06.350
Okey-dokey.

14:06.763 --> 14:08.765
You ever been in a prison?
Yes.

14:08.848 --> 14:10.316
On death row?
No.

14:10.683 --> 14:12.230
ID's again, please.

14:12.310 --> 14:16.406
All executions in the state of Texas
occur at the Huntsville unit.

14:16.481 --> 14:18.984
But death row is here
for the time being.

14:19.067 --> 14:22.742
This is home to all 442
offenders prior to their date.

14:23.112 --> 14:25.331
Average stay on
the row is nine years.

14:25.406 --> 14:28.205
Some get commuted, but
most get put to death.

14:29.369 --> 14:32.464
It'll put you off your supper,
but then, it's supposed to.

14:33.164 --> 14:34.757
GROVER: New York
guests for Mr. Gale.

14:34.874 --> 14:36.467
Can I get your bags?

14:36.542 --> 14:40.422
We have three concerns here,
safety, safety, and safety.

14:40.505 --> 14:42.599
The visitation area
is entirely secure.

14:42.673 --> 14:44.846
We just ask that you
don't touch the glass.

14:44.926 --> 14:46.678
Windex gets expensive.

14:47.220 --> 14:49.689
You're not carrying a
weapon, are you, Bitsey?

14:49.764 --> 14:51.357
(LOW AND INDISTINCT CATCALLS)

14:52.892 --> 14:54.018
Sorry. No.

14:54.310 --> 14:55.350
Mr. Stemmons, you packing?

14:55.395 --> 14:56.396
No, sir.

14:56.479 --> 14:57.446
GROVER: Cell phone?

14:57.522 --> 14:58.562
ZACK: They're not working.

14:58.606 --> 15:00.904
Then you won't mind
leaving them here.

15:00.983 --> 15:04.487
We also have rules against the
carrying of large sums of cash

15:04.570 --> 15:06.743
and the wearing
of open-toed shoes.

15:07.990 --> 15:11.085
Those will do just fine. You
want to step on through now?

15:11.577 --> 15:12.794
There you go.

15:13.162 --> 15:14.288
GUARD: Thank you, ma'am.

15:14.414 --> 15:15.506
GROVER: That's right.

15:17.041 --> 15:18.133
Open-toed shoes?

15:18.251 --> 15:19.343
Drives them crazy.

15:19.669 --> 15:22.422
GROVER: Your turn, Mr. Stemmons.
Right on through there.

15:22.672 --> 15:23.673
Good.

15:24.549 --> 15:27.553
Should anything unpleasant
occur in the visitation area,

15:27.635 --> 15:29.262
we ask you to stay put.

15:29.345 --> 15:32.565
Please follow the instructions of
our fine correctional officers

15:32.640 --> 15:34.813
should they see fit
to give you any.

15:35.643 --> 15:38.317
Anything you say
can be overheard.

15:38.396 --> 15:42.651
Any discussion of criminal activity
on your part is admissible.

15:42.733 --> 15:45.532
You're not planning on
a jailbreak, are you?

15:45.903 --> 15:48.497
The rain seems
to be holding off.

15:48.573 --> 15:52.203
You watch your step here. This
cement can get pretty slippery.

15:52.702 --> 15:54.545
This is our Japanese garden.

15:54.996 --> 15:57.875
We ask you not to
throw coins in the pond.

15:59.959 --> 16:01.882
Right this way.
Almost there.

16:03.713 --> 16:07.263
Here we are. This is our
visitation area right here.

16:08.426 --> 16:10.394
All yours, Mr. Belyeu.

16:10.470 --> 16:13.690
That's it for me. You
folks have a safe visit.

16:14.098 --> 16:15.771
Thank you.
Bye now.

16:15.850 --> 16:17.397
Ms. Bloom?
BITSEY: Yes.

16:17.560 --> 16:20.063
Come right on in here and
make yourself comfortable.

16:20.146 --> 16:22.444
Did that PR man
validate your parking?

16:22.523 --> 16:24.651
He said the gift
shop would do it.

16:25.067 --> 16:26.614
She's a smart one.

16:26.694 --> 16:28.913
Braxton Belyeu,
Mr. Gale's attorney.

16:28.988 --> 16:30.160
This is Zack Stemmons.

16:30.281 --> 16:31.453
My good pleasure.

16:31.782 --> 16:34.581
And right over here,
we have the man of the hour.

16:44.295 --> 16:45.387
Hello.

16:45.963 --> 16:47.089
Hello.
Hi.

16:47.465 --> 16:50.264
<i>GUARD (OVER P.A.): Sit down, Gale.
Prisoner will not stand.</i>

16:50.343 --> 16:52.562
Why can't they
turn that thing down?

16:53.262 --> 16:55.185
My lawyer respectfully requests

16:55.264 --> 16:58.108
that you adjust the volume
on the speaker system.

16:58.184 --> 17:01.063
<i>GUARD (OVER P.A.):
Gale, sit down.</i>

17:05.650 --> 17:07.903
They're practicing
being cruel and unusual.

17:09.819 --> 17:12.448
I'm sure you're
biting at the bit.

17:12.531 --> 17:14.375
It is our understanding
that you are

17:14.492 --> 17:16.290
to have three
two-hour sessions.

17:16.618 --> 17:18.872
Today, tomorrow, and Thursday.

17:18.954 --> 17:20.957
All at 3:00 p.m.

17:21.749 --> 17:24.047
I'm sorry we can't
afford you more time.

17:24.126 --> 17:27.756
But contrary to popular rumor,
we have not yet begun to fight.

17:28.464 --> 17:31.058
It is our understanding
that you will do this alone.

17:31.133 --> 17:33.227
The magazine would prefer that...
Alone.

17:33.302 --> 17:34.394
Understood.

17:34.470 --> 17:39.397
BELYEU: Also, you'll use no
recording equipment of any kind.

17:39.475 --> 17:41.193
BITSEY: Correct.
BELYEU: Excellent.

17:41.269 --> 17:44.364
I have a few papers for which
I need your Jo Anne Hancock.

17:44.438 --> 17:48.784
So if you'd stop by my Austin office
at your earliest convenience.

17:48.859 --> 17:50.486
Thursday morning, say?

17:50.736 --> 17:52.329
Expenses and so forth.

17:55.658 --> 17:58.332
Fine. Till Thursday, then.
Good luck.

17:58.703 --> 18:00.171
I'll stop by later.

18:02.748 --> 18:06.298
What say you and me partake
of a death-defying cigarette

18:06.377 --> 18:08.254
in the visitors' parking lot?

18:08.337 --> 18:09.429
Bye-bye, y'all.

18:18.014 --> 18:19.015
So...

18:19.765 --> 18:21.642
Please pull up a seat.

18:28.357 --> 18:29.449
He's quite a character.

18:29.525 --> 18:30.526
Yes.

18:30.610 --> 18:33.284
He's about the only outside
contact I have now.

18:33.362 --> 18:34.739
And a good friend.

18:36.073 --> 18:37.791
Where's your ex-wife?

18:37.867 --> 18:41.087
I don't want you to ask me
questions about her or my son.

18:41.871 --> 18:43.464
What I offer you is one thing.

18:43.539 --> 18:46.133
Questions about them
are not part of our deal.

18:46.208 --> 18:47.209
Okay.

18:48.085 --> 18:50.964
Just say, "Off the record,"
and I'll take it to my grave.

18:51.047 --> 18:52.594
You can trust me on that.

18:53.758 --> 18:55.977
Does this count as
recording equipment?

18:59.722 --> 19:00.894
How do we start?

19:01.015 --> 19:02.187
We start with

19:03.601 --> 19:05.774
you telling me
what I'm doing here.

19:07.396 --> 19:09.865
No one who looks through
that glass sees a person.

19:09.940 --> 19:11.317
They see a crime.

19:12.276 --> 19:15.496
I'm not David Gale.
I'm a murderer and a rapist.

19:15.571 --> 19:17.744
Four days shy of his execution.

19:19.825 --> 19:21.827
You're here because I
want to be remembered

19:21.911 --> 19:25.131
as much for howl led my life
and the decisions that I made

19:25.206 --> 19:27.254
as for how my life ended.

19:28.417 --> 19:29.634
Why me?

19:29.752 --> 19:30.924
Why not?

19:31.003 --> 19:33.597
You've spent some time behind
bars yourself recently.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.141
I certainly have.

19:35.216 --> 19:37.594
Because you do take
things to your grave.

